node.title: Victoria records 1,254 new COVID-19 cases and five deaths as state hits 90pc double vaccination threshold
node.alt: Pedestrians wearing masks cross the road in front of Flinders Street Station in Melbourne
node.description: VictoriaÂ reaches its target of 90 per cent full vaccination for those aged 12 and over. There are 10,276 active COVID-19 cases in the state.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,254\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and five\u00a0deaths, as the state reaches its target of 90 per cent full vaccination for those aged 12 and over.", "There are now 10,276\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 487\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 310\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 48\u00a0are in intensive care and 31\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 48\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "More to come.", "", "
